<big>'''What is Namecoin'''</big>

[[Namecoin]] is a peer-to-peer '''generic''' name/value datastore system based on [http://www.bitcoin.org/ Bitcoin] technology (a decentralized cryptocurrency).
It allows you to:
* Securely register and transfer arbitrary names, '''no possible censorship!'''
* Attach values to the names (up to 1023 bytes)
* Trade and transact namecoins, the digital currency '''NMC'''.

There are plenty of possible [[use cases]]. Read more about [[Namecoin]].


<big>'''What is Dot-BIT'''</big>

Dot-BIT, the first project using namecoin, is building a domain name system ('''DNS''') using the '''.bit TLD'''.
Our goal is to spread .bit domains by providing resources and tools to the community, from developers to end users.


